 You see this next feature in action.

98
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:02,100
 So here's a couple things we can do.

99
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:05,180
 So there is this user object that in a sense is passed in.

100
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:07,440
 You don't have to do anything to pass it in.

101
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:09,380
 There's this user object that sits there

102
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:13,380
 in your template context that's automatically.

103
00:04:13,380 --> 00:04:15,620
 We'll talk later about how you can sort of inject

104
00:04:15,620 --> 00:04:19,140
 into every template certain little things

105
00:04:19,140 --> 00:04:20,220
 that you gotta inject.

106
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:22,580
 But the system injects this user.

107
00:04:22,580 --> 00:04:25,220
 There is an attribute called isAuthenticated,

108
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:26,820
 which is true or false,

109
00:04:26,820 --> 00:04:29,760
 to say whether you're not logged in or are logged in.

110
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:33,580
 And so if we see it, we say,

111
00:04:33,580 --> 00:04:35,340
 oh, what's their person's full name?

112
00:04:35,340 --> 00:04:37,940
 User.email, user.id.

113
00:04:37,940 --> 00:04:39,460
 User id is the primary key.

114
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:42,460
 We might actually have a, later we'll have a foreign key

115
00:04:42,460 --> 00:04:44,020
 that goes into the user table.

116
00:04:44,020 --> 00:04:45,660
 And we need to know what the primary key

117
00:04:45,660 --> 00:04:49,260
 of the current user is so we can populate our foreign key

118
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:52,140
 so when we like have a row and it's owned by such and so,

119
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:53,900
 we're gonna actually put a foreign key into a table

120
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:55,880
 that we didn't even create.

121
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:57,340
 But the thing I'm talking about now

122
00:04:57,340 --> 00:05:00,300
 is you can get a URL, that URL tag,

123
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:02,180
 that's looking up the name of a view.

124
00:05:02,180 --> 00:05:04,020
 Log out is the name of a view.

125
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:05,780
 Log in is the name of a view.

126
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:07,840
 And then we have this question mark next equals.

127
00:05:07,840 --> 00:05:10,940
 That's the parameter to say when you're all done

128
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:15,340
 with that login or log out, go back to this particular URL.

129
00:05:15,340 --> 00:05:20,340
 Okay, and so that says go to the URL

130
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:25,820
 that's in the Authsy application, the view named open.

131
00:05:25,820 --> 00:05:28,580
 And so that's one way of doing it.

132
00:05:28,580 --> 00:05:30,380
 Another way, let's say you're in login,

133
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:31,540
 we're gonna get the login URL

134
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:33,820
 and send ourselves back to the request path.

135
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:36,220
 Request is another one of these things

136
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:38,560
 that's dropped in automatically for us.

137
00:05:38,560 --> 00:05:41,820
 That is the current URL of the view we're at.

138
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:45,300
 So in a sense, this is a contraction

139
00:05:45,300 --> 00:05:47,340
 that says go ahead and go to login,

140
00:05:47,340 --> 00:05:49,380
 and when you're back, come right back here.

141
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:51,880
 So login will login and then redirect

142
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:54,760
 back to this page that we're on, whatever the page is.

143
